messages.message:
@Liam Callanan we’re already using `<Input type="number" />` from Pollen in this case (https://github.com/instabase/javascript-packages/blob/b7403ab/packages/doc-widget/src/docWidget/Toolbar.tsx#L205-L219)

to not show keywords, i guess we need to set `autocomplete="off"` - should this be done for all `type="number"` cases?

for the +/-/. characters, i don’t think there’s a way to disallow +/-/. characters with pure html (spec (https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/input.html#number-state-(type%3Dnumber)) allows for floating points) - should we add a `type="count"` to disallow non-numeric characters?
